1 Extreme base of cerci subequal in width to the space between them (
<figureCitation box="[882,941,725,747]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1918,1941]" captionTargetBox="[312,1283,1193,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[312,1283,1193,1901]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 4 – 7. Perigomphus basicornis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 4) Dorsal view of S 9 – 10 showing the caudal appendages. 5) Left latero-dorsal view of caudal appendages. 6) Left lateral view (slightly ventral) of caudal appendages. 7) S 8 – 10 and caudal appendages, ventral view. a = arm of epiproct, Ah = anterior hamuli, Ce = cerci, Ep = epiproct, p = baso-lateral process of cerci, Ph = posterior hamulus. Pr = dorsolateral process of paraproct, sbvh = sub-basal ventral horn of cerci." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/832660/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="398">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
); mesal carinate margin of cerci entire, not notched subapically (
<figureCitation box="[347,437,755,777]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1918,1941]" captionTargetBox="[312,1283,1193,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[312,1283,1193,1901]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 4 – 7. Perigomphus basicornis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 4) Dorsal view of S 9 – 10 showing the caudal appendages. 5) Left latero-dorsal view of caudal appendages. 6) Left lateral view (slightly ventral) of caudal appendages. 7) S 8 – 10 and caudal appendages, ventral view. a = arm of epiproct, Ah = anterior hamuli, Ce = cerci, Ep = epiproct, p = baso-lateral process of cerci, Ph = posterior hamulus. Pr = dorsolateral process of paraproct, sbvh = sub-basal ventral horn of cerci." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/832660/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="398">Figs. 4, 5</figureCitation>
)......................................................................... 
