</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,725,953]" pageId="3" pageNumber="398">
<keyLead pageId="3" pageNumber="398">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,159,784,806]" pageId="3" pageNumber="398">-</emphasis>
Extreme base of cerci notoriously shorter than space between them; mesal carinate margin of cerci notched subapically (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 11" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1664,1687]" captionTargetBox="[214,1371,264,1557]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,235,1596]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 11. Perigomphus spp. 8) Dorsal view of S 10 and caudal appendages of male of P. angularis; 9) the same, lateral view; 10) Dorsal view of S 10 and caudal appendages of male of P. pallidistylus; 11) the same, lateral view. a = arm of epiproct, Ce = cerci, Ep = epiproct, ma = medial angle, p = baso-lateral process of cerci, Pr = dorsolateral process of paraproct, san = subapical notch, sbvp = sub-basal ventral projection of cerci. Figs. 8 – 9 after Tennessen (2011); Figs. 10 – 11 after Belle (1972)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/832662/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="398">Figs. 8, 10</figureCitation>
)............................................................................................... 2
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="3" pageNumber="398">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,725,953]" pageId="3" pageNumber="398">
<keyLead pageId="3" pageNumber="398">
