<figureCitation box="[349,407,872,894]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 11" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1664,1687]" captionTargetBox="[214,1371,264,1557]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,235,1596]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 11. Perigomphus spp. 8) Dorsal view of S 10 and caudal appendages of male of P. angularis; 9) the same, lateral view; 10) Dorsal view of S 10 and caudal appendages of male of P. pallidistylus; 11) the same, lateral view. a = arm of epiproct, Ce = cerci, Ep = epiproct, ma = medial angle, p = baso-lateral process of cerci, Pr = dorsolateral process of paraproct, san = subapical notch, sbvp = sub-basal ventral projection of cerci. Figs. 8 – 9 after Tennessen (2011); Figs. 10 – 11 after Belle (1972)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/832662/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="398">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
); in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[576,634,872,894]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 11" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1664,1687]" captionTargetBox="[214,1371,264,1557]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,235,1596]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 11. Perigomphus spp. 8) Dorsal view of S 10 and caudal appendages of male of P. angularis; 9) the same, lateral view; 10) Dorsal view of S 10 and caudal appendages of male of P. pallidistylus; 11) the same, lateral view. a = arm of epiproct, Ce = cerci, Ep = epiproct, ma = medial angle, p = baso-lateral process of cerci, Pr = dorsolateral process of paraproct, san = subapical notch, sbvp = sub-basal ventral projection of cerci. Figs. 8 – 9 after Tennessen (2011); Figs. 10 – 11 after Belle (1972)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/832662/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="398">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
) with a vestigial sub-basal projection............................. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tennessen" authorityYear="2011" box="[1343,1435,872,894]" class="Insecta" family="Gomphidae" genus="Perigomphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="3" pageNumber="398" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angularis">
<emphasis box="[1343,1435,872,894]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="398">angularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
